&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Executive Personal Assistant &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and experienced Executive Personal Assistant to join our Medical Directorate. You will be providing full Executive support to the Medical Director and support to the Primary Care Lead and wider team. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Typical duties will include complex diary and calendar support, overseeing multiple tasks and working with the wider teams to ensure deadlines are met, as well as coordinating and minuting meetings. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This role requires excellent attention to detail and accuracy. You will have good communication skills, be organised, friendly, confident, methodical and computer literate. &lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview’s will be week commencing 30th November. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
